00:00:09.156 --> 00:00:14.122 position:7% line:77% align:start
(NARRATOR) <i>In his memory, she</i>
 <i>lives on. Her humanity, her</i>
 <i>resilience...</i>

00:00:15.122 --> 00:00:20.122 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>Michelle, too, looks inward ,</i>
 <i>recalling her mentor and source</i>
 <i>of strength.</i>

00:00:20.790 --> 00:00:26.623 position:10% line:77% align:start
 <i>To them, it was a reason to</i>
 <i>fight. To them it was a reason</i>
 <i>to live.</i>

00:00:26.890 --> 00:00:29.790 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>But just as the battle appears</i>
 <i>to have closed...</i>

00:00:32.090 --> 00:00:34.490 position:10% line:5% align:start
It's in your hands now Alex.

00:00:35.058 --> 00:00:35.757 position:27% line:89% align:start
[throwing grunt]

00:00:36.524 --> 00:00:36.824 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:00:37.791 --> 00:00:39.457 position:10% line:89% align:start
I'm gonna haunt your dreams.

00:00:40.958 --> 00:00:41.524 position:41% line:89% align:start
Huh?!

00:00:42.024 --> 00:00:43.490 position:24% line:89% align:start
It... didn't work?

00:02:16.731 --> 00:02:19.031 position:5% line:83% align:start
I was so sure I was gonna pitch
a strike...

00:02:19.065 --> 00:02:21.799 position:21% line:77% align:start
but all of a sudden
the "batter" changed his
swing...

00:02:22.232 --> 00:02:24.699 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>Now why didn't they fire a</i>
 <i>second missle?</i>

00:02:24.732 --> 00:02:26.799 position:7% line:83% align:start
(YAEKO) <i>Maybe the plan worked,</i>
 <i>after all?</i>

00:02:26.999 --> 00:02:30.066 position:5% line:77% align:start
We know we succeeded in making
them waste one of their
missles...

00:02:30.099 --> 00:02:32.966 position:16% line:77% align:start
but we failed to
create a smoke signal to
get help.

00:02:32.999 --> 00:02:36.100 position:5% line:83% align:start
So I guess it was a partial
victory. Ah!

00:02:36.133 --> 00:02:36.800 position:78% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:37.800 position:5% line:89% align:start
[painful groans]

00:02:37.833 --> 00:02:38.466 position:80% line:89% align:start
Alex!

00:02:39.533 --> 00:02:42.967 position:10% line:83% align:start
Akari and Michelle have been
located. Retrieving.

00:02:45.733 --> 00:02:46.499 position:27% line:89% align:start
[unsteady gasp]

00:02:52.701 --> 00:02:54.701 position:27% line:89% align:start
[pained breaths]

00:02:54.734 --> 00:02:56.667 position:7% line:83% align:start
(BAO) <i>It's been a while... XO</i>
 <i>Davis.</i>

00:02:57.034 --> 00:03:00.101 position:7% line:83% align:start
My name's Bao Zhilan, I'm with
Squad 4, Rank 50.

00:03:00.802 --> 00:03:04.835 position:5% line:77% align:start
After today's events, I'm afraid
I'm obliged to take you and
Hizamaru prisoner.

00:03:05.269 --> 00:03:07.969 position:7% line:5% align:start
(MICHELLE) <i>That's an airbike.</i>
 <i>Was he tailing us?</i>

00:03:08.002 --> 00:03:09.969 position:7% line:83% align:start
(BAO) <i>You two must be in a lot</i>
 <i>of pain.</i>

00:03:12.269 --> 00:03:16.970 position:5% line:77% align:start
[blowing air and chuckling] Wow,
would you look at that--you've
both fractured your lower jaws.

00:03:17.636 --> 00:03:22.970 position:7% line:77% align:start
Same with your clavicles. Ribs
too! You've both earned some
nasty cerebral contusions...

00:03:23.736 --> 00:03:27.870 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>My guess is you probably have</i>
 <i>multiple skull fractures too. Am</i>
 <i>I right? </i>

00:03:27.904 --> 00:03:30.204 position:24% line:77% align:start
 <i>With injuries like</i>
 <i>that, I'm surprised you</i>
 <i>can...</i>

00:03:30.237 --> 00:03:33.171 position:21% line:77% align:start
 <i>still muster up the</i>
 <i>strength to shoot me that</i>
 <i>angry look.</i>

00:03:33.804 --> 00:03:36.971 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>The drugs ran out at just the</i>
 <i>right time. For me, that is.</i>

00:03:37.971 --> 00:03:38.804 position:33% line:89% align:start
Now then...

00:03:41.272 --> 00:03:41.805 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:03:42.272 --> 00:03:42.738 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:03:45.072 --> 00:03:47.138 position:7% line:83% align:start
The First and Second have been
secured...

00:03:48.272 --> 00:03:52.138 position:5% line:83% align:start
...along with 200 roach samples
obtained by the US-Japan Squad.

00:03:52.671 --> 00:03:53.638 position:30% line:89% align:start
Not bad work!

00:03:54.039 --> 00:03:54.806 position:27% line:89% align:start
[pained grunts]

00:03:55.772 --> 00:03:57.472 position:5% line:83% align:start
Please just sit tight and behave
yourselves.

00:03:58.739 --> 00:03:59.973 position:21% line:77% align:start
Though it's not like
you could move even if you
wanted to.

00:04:00.239 --> 00:04:02.039 position:5% line:83% align:start
What happened to Captain
Komachi?

00:04:02.073 --> 00:04:03.206 position:38% line:89% align:start
No idea.

00:04:03.239 --> 00:04:05.206 position:21% line:89% align:start
Liar! Don't screw with us!

00:04:05.239 --> 00:04:07.640 position:19% line:83% align:start
You're not getting any
information from me.

00:04:07.673 --> 00:04:08.007 position:24% line:89% align:start
[frustrated grunt]

00:04:09.274 --> 00:04:10.640 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>(BAO) Remember, I'm the one who</i>
 <i>gets to ask the questions here.</i>

00:04:11.573 --> 00:04:13.506 position:13% line:83% align:start
You should know, this plan
wasn't easy.

00:04:15.140 --> 00:04:17.807 position:10% line:77% align:start
We had no idea how many crew
members your squad still had on
board your vehicles.

00:04:18.174 --> 00:04:23.674 position:5% line:77% align:start
We weren't sure if you two were
the only survivors. And ideally,
we wanted to capture you alive.

00:04:27.741 --> 00:04:29.541 position:5% line:83% align:start
But we found out there were
others!

00:04:29.574 --> 00:04:32.607 position:24% line:77% align:start
Like that panicky
low-ranking girl who scares
easily.

00:04:32.641 --> 00:04:36.809 position:5% line:77% align:start
She responded from Vehicle 2.
And Rank 12 was with you as
well.

00:04:37.209 --> 00:04:37.976 position:21% line:89% align:start
[frustrated grunts]

00:04:39.608 --> 00:04:41.709 position:5% line:77% align:start
(BAO) <i>Don't worry. We won't kill</i>
 <i>them if we don't have to. After</i>
 <i>all... </i>

00:04:41.742 --> 00:04:43.976 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>we're all part of the</i>
 <i>same team, right?</i>

00:04:47.776 --> 00:04:50.643 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Well, here's our next mystery of</i>
 <i>the day...</i>

00:04:52.977 --> 00:04:57.643 position:5% line:77% align:start
Vehicle 1 in unmanned. So where
did the rest of Squads 1 and 2
go?

00:05:00.877 --> 00:05:01.544 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sigh]

00:05:02.211 --> 00:05:03.644 position:44% line:89% align:start
 <i>They're all dead.</i>

00:05:05.445 --> 00:05:10.477 position:5% line:5% align:start
The roaches... we've fought them
twice already, and lost everyone
before the Paraponera came.

00:05:12.744 --> 00:05:13.477 position:30% line:89% align:start
[pained grunt]

00:05:14.678 --> 00:05:15.045 position:38% line:89% align:start
Monster!

00:05:15.979 --> 00:05:17.145 position:30% line:5% align:start
[pained groan]

00:05:19.012 --> 00:05:20.478 position:30% line:89% align:start
You bastard...

00:05:20.511 --> 00:05:25.812 position:13% line:77% align:start
Oh? Insectile half-breeds
experience pain too?! That's so
interesting.

00:05:26.645 --> 00:05:27.846 position:19% line:89% align:start
You've got real guts.

00:05:28.046 --> 00:05:28.913 position:30% line:89% align:start
[tense breath]

00:05:29.879 --> 00:05:31.579 position:7% line:83% align:start
Time to come clean. Where are
the others?

00:05:31.779 --> 00:05:32.646 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:05:33.913 --> 00:05:35.646 position:7% line:83% align:start
(BAO) <i>Specifically, where are</i>
 <i>Rank 8 and Rank 9?</i>

00:05:36.713 --> 00:05:38.980 position:16% line:83% align:start
You're in command, Michelle.
What are our orders?

00:05:39.013 --> 00:05:40.480 position:10% line:89% align:start
How can we get the upper hand?

00:05:42.348 --> 00:05:45.547 position:13% line:77% align:start
(MICHELLE) <i>When it comes to</i>
 <i>Squad 4, we have two pathes to</i>
 <i>victory before us.</i>

00:05:45.580 --> 00:05:48.114 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>One is direct</i>
 <i>and the other is indirect.</i>

00:05:48.147 --> 00:05:49.147 position:41% line:89% align:start
 <i>Here's our plan...</i>

00:05:50.547 --> 00:05:53.647 position:21% line:77% align:start
(BAO) <i>Where are the</i>
 <i>noncombatants from Squads 1 and</i>
 <i>2?</i>

00:05:56.748 --> 00:06:00.648 position:5% line:83% align:start
Sunset? My, my, where does the
time go?

00:06:02.581 --> 00:06:03.148 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:06:04.148 --> 00:06:05.648 position:24% line:83% align:start
Don't get any ideas about
trying to escape.

00:06:07.183 --> 00:06:10.649 position:13% line:77% align:start
Good news: I've secured First
and Second. Requesting pickup,
General Liu.

00:06:11.283 --> 00:06:13.649 position:30% line:83% align:start
 Affirmative. I'm on my
way.

00:06:14.949 --> 00:06:16.916 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'll start heading back with
Vehicle 1...

00:06:16.949 --> 00:06:20.283 position:21% line:77% align:start
but I don't see any
other personnel from Squads 1
and 2.

00:06:20.316 --> 00:06:22.516 position:27% line:83% align:start
Their whereabouts remain
unknown.

00:06:25.550 --> 00:06:27.117 position:13% line:83% align:start
(MARCOS) <i>It's almost night up</i>
 <i>there.</i>

00:06:27.150 --> 00:06:28.984 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>They'll be sending out patrols</i>
 <i>now.</i>

00:06:29.250 --> 00:06:32.616 position:5% line:83% align:start
Good. We'll crush those traitors
when they least expect it.

00:06:35.285 --> 00:06:39.551 position:7% line:77% align:start
(MICHELLE) <i>They've modified the</i>
 <i>communications tower into a</i>
 <i>jammer blocking transmissions.</i>

00:06:39.584 --> 00:06:42.651 position:35% line:77% align:start
 <i>We seize the tower</i>
 <i>and transmit Squad 4's</i>
 <i>betrayal.</i>

00:06:44.051 --> 00:06:46.651 position:7% line:83% align:start
That will spur all the factions
on Earth into action.

00:06:47.186 --> 00:06:50.152 position:38% line:77% align:start
That is
how we will defeat Squad 4
indirectly.

00:06:51.652 --> 00:06:53.119 position:41% line:89% align:start
[exhausted breaths]

00:06:53.152 --> 00:06:54.652 position:33% line:89% align:start
You doing okay, Peggy?

00:06:55.652 --> 00:06:57.752 position:47% line:89% align:start
[catching breath]

00:07:00.252 --> 00:07:02.220 position:10% line:83% align:start
How much farther before we get
there, Jared?

00:07:02.619 --> 00:07:06.820 position:5% line:77% align:start
Well, I know we're past the
mines. I'd say 500 meters to
Annex 1.

00:07:07.253 --> 00:07:10.886 position:10% line:83% align:start
500 meeters, huh? Can I take a
little break?

00:07:10.920 --> 00:07:11.586 position:5% line:89% align:start
Sure.

00:07:11.619 --> 00:07:12.486 position:66% line:89% align:start
I'm sorry.

00:07:13.686 --> 00:07:16.487 position:5% line:83% align:start
Don't appologize. You're just as
human as the rest of us.

00:07:16.754 --> 00:07:18.721 position:44% line:77% align:start
You
just happen to have echidna
claws.

00:07:18.754 --> 00:07:22.221 position:7% line:77% align:start
He's right! Plus, we've got to
stay underground for the rest of
the night.

00:07:22.254 --> 00:07:23.188 position:44% line:89% align:start
Wait, why do that?

00:07:24.221 --> 00:07:26.954 position:10% line:83% align:start
Hundreds of biomagnetic fields
just disappeared.

00:07:26.988 --> 00:07:31.222 position:10% line:77% align:start
There's a chance it was poison
gas, a biological weapon, or
radiation.

00:07:31.255 --> 00:07:33.555 position:21% line:83% align:start
But I know it wasn't
a nuclear explosion.

00:07:33.588 --> 00:07:36.222 position:10% line:83% align:start
You sure? They'd really use
something like that?

00:07:36.255 --> 00:07:41.223 position:13% line:77% align:start
M-hm. I sensed about 500
biomagnetic fields rushing the
annex...

00:07:41.256 --> 00:07:43.156 position:5% line:83% align:start
they were probably
terraformars.

00:07:44.756 --> 00:07:47.090 position:5% line:77% align:start
But then, once they arrived at
that very location they
completely disappeared.

00:07:47.123 --> 00:07:48.556 position:19% line:83% align:start
They
died instantly.

00:07:48.589 --> 00:07:49.990 position:5% line:83% align:start
But I didn't sense a
thing.

00:07:51.390 --> 00:07:54.057 position:5% line:77% align:start
Your procedure base is killer
whale, which senses through
sonar.

00:07:54.091 --> 00:07:55.790 position:5% line:83% align:start
Mine is hammerhead
shark...

00:07:55.824 --> 00:07:58.824 position:5% line:83% align:start
I detect biomagnetic fields in
all living things.

00:07:59.157 --> 00:08:04.091 position:5% line:77% align:start
The fact is... a sudden death of
that size means Squad 4 has a
weapon of mass destruction.

00:08:04.124 --> 00:08:04.458 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:08:05.590 --> 00:08:06.890 position:16% line:83% align:start
Then our plan won't work. We
can't get close to them!

00:08:06.924 --> 00:08:09.158 position:5% line:89% align:start
We can. We will. We have to.

00:08:09.825 --> 00:08:13.891 position:10% line:77% align:start
We're engineers! This is the
kind of challenge our minds were
made for.

00:08:13.925 --> 00:08:15.992 position:10% line:83% align:start
We'll put our heads
together and solve this!

00:08:16.791 --> 00:08:20.225 position:5% line:83% align:start
[chuckle] You sure talk big for
being only rank 90.

00:08:20.258 --> 00:08:21.492 position:61% line:89% align:start
I'm serious.

00:08:21.692 --> 00:08:22.859 position:52% line:5% align:start
You got a plan?

00:08:23.993 --> 00:08:26.559 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's unlikely to be radiation.
So we wait until dawn.

00:08:27.193 --> 00:08:28.159 position:5% line:89% align:start
We should wait?

00:08:29.592 --> 00:08:31.926 position:5% line:77% align:start
(WOLF) The morning sunlight will
burn through any remaining
bacteria.

00:08:31.959 --> 00:08:34.727 position:5% line:83% align:start
And the wind will blow away any
residual poison.

00:08:34.994 --> 00:08:38.560 position:5% line:83% align:start
We need to stage a distraction.
If we can shift their focus --

00:08:38.593 --> 00:08:40.560 position:5% line:83% align:start
for a minute or even thirty
seconds...

00:08:40.593 --> 00:08:43.660 position:16% line:77% align:start
we should be able
to infultrate the Annex's
communications room.

00:08:44.060 --> 00:08:47.261 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Once we're in, we hack the</i>
 <i>communications tower. </i>

00:08:47.295 --> 00:08:50.228 position:38% line:77% align:start
 <i>Gaining</i>
 <i>control of the system shouldn't</i>
 <i>be difficult. </i>

00:08:50.261 --> 00:08:53.161 position:27% line:77% align:start
 <i>Remember,</i>
 <i>engineers like us set the</i>
 <i>thing up.</i>

00:08:53.894 --> 00:08:58.761 position:10% line:77% align:start
And that's when we send the
message to Earth: Squad 4 has
betrayed all of us!

00:08:59.295 --> 00:09:01.662 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>They were clever but they</i>
 <i>underestimated us. </i>

00:09:01.996 --> 00:09:05.695 position:33% line:77% align:start
 <i>They didn't</i>
 <i>realize we'd fight back with</i>
 <i>every ounce of our strength.</i>

00:09:06.029 --> 00:09:08.795 position:5% line:83% align:start
Sorry about the jerky wise crack
back there Wolf.

00:09:09.029 --> 00:09:09.929 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'm in!

00:09:11.628 --> 00:09:15.596 position:13% line:77% align:start
Thank you. Actually, the
best I can do is help us figure
out how to solve problems.

00:09:15.629 --> 00:09:17.963 position:5% line:83% align:start
We need your skills to fight the
Terraformars.

00:09:18.830 --> 00:09:22.063 position:5% line:83% align:start
That said, I'll put my life on
the line if I need to.

00:09:22.663 --> 00:09:28.231 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>Akari... Michelle. The two of</i>
 <i>them are Squad 4's primary</i>
 <i>targets, so they could've hid.</i>

00:09:28.264 --> 00:09:30.731 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>But they put themselves in</i>
 <i>danger to protect us.</i>

00:09:30.764 --> 00:09:32.231 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>Alex and Yaeko, did too...</i>

00:09:33.864 --> 00:09:36.998 position:5% line:77% align:start
So now it's our turn to protect
them. our powers were never
meant for combat...

00:09:37.031 --> 00:09:38.831 position:38% line:77% align:start
but that
can't keep us away from
the fight!

00:09:39.031 --> 00:09:39.998 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm with you!

00:09:41.065 --> 00:09:42.199 position:16% line:89% align:start
We can't let them down.

00:09:44.698 --> 00:09:45.865 position:38% line:5% align:start
 <i>Sheila.</i>

00:09:57.632 --> 00:09:59.833 position:5% line:89% align:start
[anguished grunt] <i>Forgive me!</i>

00:10:00.300 --> 00:10:02.966 position:5% line:5% align:start
I was there, but I couldn't... I
tried...

00:10:04.233 --> 00:10:05.499 position:35% line:89% align:start
Sheila...

00:10:07.334 --> 00:10:08.900 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:10:10.001 --> 00:10:10.500 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:10:13.234 --> 00:10:14.500 position:19% line:89% align:start
[struggling to breath]

00:10:15.633 --> 00:10:17.234 position:16% line:83% align:start
Why did we end up coming all
this way to Mars, Marcos?

00:10:17.267 --> 00:10:18.834 position:5% line:89% align:start
In order to protect... Sheila--

00:10:20.267 --> 00:10:22.868 position:7% line:77% align:start
Oh really? Then it seems to me
you're appologizing to the wrong
person.

00:10:22.901 --> 00:10:24.701 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm here for a different
reason.

00:10:26.302 --> 00:10:29.335 position:5% line:77% align:start
For as long as we've been alive,
we've been nothing but pawns to
the world...

00:10:29.369 --> 00:10:31.835 position:35% line:83% align:start
Waiting patiently
for it to toss us aside.

00:10:33.701 --> 00:10:36.069 position:5% line:83% align:start
Well Marcos, I came here to
change all that!

00:10:36.103 --> 00:10:40.203 position:10% line:77% align:start
That's why you're here too!
We're fighting for a better life
back home.

00:10:44.635 --> 00:10:46.736 position:38% line:89% align:start
[crying]

00:10:46.769 --> 00:10:49.137 position:30% line:89% align:start
We'll take our revenge.

00:10:49.170 --> 00:10:52.037 position:38% line:89% align:start
[crying]

00:10:54.170 --> 00:10:57.503 position:16% line:77% align:start
(WOLF) <i>There's one more</i>
 <i>possibility for this weapon of</i>
 <i>mass destruction.</i>

00:10:57.703 --> 00:10:58.170 position:78% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:10:59.636 --> 00:11:01.771 position:10% line:77% align:start
...It isn't a "weapon" at all,
but a human with bacteria-type
power.

00:11:03.271 --> 00:11:05.838 position:24% line:77% align:start
A person who emanates
infection. Their only purpose
is spreading death.

00:11:06.071 --> 00:11:07.771 position:7% line:83% align:start
Of course that's where you come
in.

00:11:08.071 --> 00:11:08.671 position:75% line:89% align:start
Got it.

00:11:08.704 --> 00:11:08.804 position:41% line:89% align:start
Okay.

00:11:10.438 --> 00:11:14.505 position:5% line:77% align:start
Stay safe, everyone. We're gonna
bust those Squad 4 traitors'
heads wide open...

00:11:14.839 --> 00:11:16.872 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>and make it</i>
 <i>back home to Earth!</i>

00:11:21.006 --> 00:11:21.505 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:11:23.272 --> 00:11:23.605 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:11:25.972 --> 00:11:28.173 position:33% line:89% align:start
Huh... Hmph!

00:11:28.873 --> 00:11:32.940 position:10% line:77% align:start
Damn it! The Terraformars
spotted us and set a trap for
our vehicle...

00:11:32.973 --> 00:11:34.706 position:21% line:89% align:start
I think that was a signal!

00:11:35.040 --> 00:11:39.007 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>The two we fought earlier were</i>
 <i>just delaying us.</i>

00:11:39.040 --> 00:11:41.241 position:7% line:83% align:start
I thought all personal weapons,
like this sword...

00:11:41.274 --> 00:11:43.841 position:41% line:77% align:start
would have
been embedded with powerful
security-lock systems.

00:11:44.174 --> 00:11:47.674 position:10% line:77% align:start
But it seems they've set it up
so that shipmates can use these
things too.

00:12:03.009 --> 00:12:05.009 position:21% line:83% align:start
(SHOKICHI) <i>Can't we go any</i>
 <i>faster?</i>

00:12:05.042 --> 00:12:07.075 position:7% line:5% align:start
This craft is an older model.

00:12:07.109 --> 00:12:10.576 position:13% line:5% align:start
At this rate, we'll never be
able to catch up with Michelle
and Akari.

00:12:10.876 --> 00:12:12.676 position:16% line:89% align:start
Plus, it's almost nightfall.

00:12:14.310 --> 00:12:17.843 position:5% line:77% align:start
Uh huh. And this one is gonna be
a different kind of night. Be
ready for combat.

00:12:18.909 --> 00:12:23.810 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>This may be the Terraformars</i>
 <i>biggest attack since our first</i>
 <i>day here. Buckle up. </i>

00:12:23.844 --> 00:12:26.777 position:33% line:77% align:start
 <i>I have a</i>
 <i>feeling those bugs are going</i>
 <i>to surprise us.</i>

00:12:29.944 --> 00:12:34.511 position:7% line:77% align:start
I'm going to cut through them,
Hizamaru. And then I'm taking
you back alive.

00:12:49.779 --> 00:12:55.179 position:7% line:83% align:start
This... is crazy! He's crazy!
There's no way he'll survive!

00:13:00.847 --> 00:13:01.680 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:13:02.847 --> 00:13:03.513 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:13:05.280 --> 00:13:08.014 position:21% line:5% align:start
 <i>Strange... Why isn't</i>
 <i>he mutating?! Doesn't he have</i>
 <i>any combat powers?</i>

00:13:08.847 --> 00:13:10.680 position:16% line:5% align:start
 <i>His fighting skills are</i>
 <i>incredible.</i>

00:13:11.314 --> 00:13:13.347 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunting]

00:13:13.381 --> 00:13:15.748 position:13% line:83% align:start
(AKARI) <i>That's no ordinary</i>
 <i>swordsmanship.</i>

00:13:15.781 --> 00:13:15.948 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hm?

00:13:16.848 --> 00:13:17.514 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:13:20.614 --> 00:13:23.881 position:16% line:5% align:start
(AKARI) <i>But none of that</i>
 <i>matters! There's too many of</i>
 <i>them!</i>

00:13:25.315 --> 00:13:28.182 position:10% line:5% align:start
 <i>There are thousands of them!</i>
 <i>He'll never make it!</i>

00:13:29.915 --> 00:13:31.849 position:16% line:89% align:start
This <i>is</i> looking futile.

00:13:35.316 --> 00:13:35.849 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:13:36.082 --> 00:13:36.749 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:13:36.782 --> 00:13:37.682 position:41% line:89% align:start
Huh?!

00:13:37.915 --> 00:13:39.849 position:5% line:89% align:start
Nothing a few decoys can't fix.

00:13:40.316 --> 00:13:44.050 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>The Terraformars target enemies</i>
 <i>according to a specific</i>
 <i>heirarchy.</i>

00:13:44.317 --> 00:13:49.983 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>First they attack anyone with a</i>
 <i>tool, or the tools themselves,</i>
 <i>especially if they're good ones.</i>

00:13:50.017 --> 00:13:55.684 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>Second they attack anyone alone.</i>
 <i>Third they attack anyone</i>
 <i>injured. And fourth... </i>

00:13:55.717 --> 00:13:58.184 position:38% line:77% align:start
 <i>for some</i>
 <i>reason they love to go</i>
 <i>after women.</i>

00:14:02.917 --> 00:14:05.084 position:41% line:89% align:start
Oh no!

00:14:05.118 --> 00:14:06.184 position:30% line:89% align:start
(ALEX) <i>Yaeko!</i>

00:14:07.618 --> 00:14:11.052 position:41% line:89% align:start
Ahhh!

00:14:11.085 --> 00:14:12.252 position:21% line:89% align:start
[grunts and groans]

00:14:12.818 --> 00:14:13.618 position:35% line:89% align:start
No, Alex!

00:14:13.818 --> 00:14:14.618 position:41% line:89% align:start
Yaeko!

00:14:15.185 --> 00:14:16.019 position:19% line:89% align:start
[grunts and whimpers]

00:14:18.052 --> 00:14:21.753 position:5% line:77% align:start
(BAO) <i>We don't know why they go</i>
 <i>after women. It's not for sexual</i>
 <i>gratification. It's eerie... </i>

00:14:21.786 --> 00:14:23.853 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>but something definitely</i>
 <i>attracts them.</i>

00:14:24.186 --> 00:14:27.186 position:16% line:89% align:start
Stop this! You bastard!

00:14:29.886 --> 00:14:32.586 position:5% line:89% align:start
[groaning] A-Alex? Why'd you...

00:14:33.586 --> 00:14:33.987 position:80% line:89% align:start
Why?!

00:14:34.620 --> 00:14:36.720 position:24% line:89% align:start
Why haven't you mutated?!

00:14:36.754 --> 00:14:41.154 position:5% line:83% align:start
[chuckle] Good question. I don't
know...

00:14:41.687 --> 00:14:47.188 position:10% line:77% align:start
I mean. I know that if I can't
transform, I'm just in the way
on our mission. It's weird.

00:14:48.122 --> 00:14:49.755 position:5% line:89% align:start
Maybe I wanted to impress you.

00:14:49.788 --> 00:14:50.554 position:78% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:14:52.122 --> 00:14:56.022 position:16% line:77% align:start
Because I knew that you were
watching me. Do you remember
back at the shrine...

00:15:00.322 --> 00:15:03.089 position:19% line:83% align:start
You didn't come back. I was
getting worried about you.

00:15:03.356 --> 00:15:04.189 position:41% line:89% align:start
Sorry.

00:15:05.922 --> 00:15:07.555 position:30% line:89% align:start
The bugs aren't coming.

00:15:07.889 --> 00:15:08.689 position:41% line:89% align:start
Good.

00:15:10.123 --> 00:15:11.189 position:86% line:89% align:start
Hm?

00:15:11.689 --> 00:15:13.023 position:78% line:89% align:start
[sigh]

00:15:21.690 --> 00:15:24.024 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm sorry about Sheila.

00:15:24.224 --> 00:15:25.124 position:38% line:89% align:start
Thanks.

00:15:25.157 --> 00:15:27.090 position:16% line:89% align:start
She was special to you, huh?

00:15:27.124 --> 00:15:27.858 position:41% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:15:28.624 --> 00:15:30.524 position:33% line:83% align:start
She made the unltimate
sacrifice.

00:15:30.891 --> 00:15:31.858 position:41% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:15:34.657 --> 00:15:38.058 position:7% line:83% align:start
But... She shouldn't have come
to Mars in the first place.

00:15:40.859 --> 00:15:44.159 position:10% line:83% align:start
I wasn't there when she was
killed but even if I had been...

00:15:44.192 --> 00:15:46.625 position:5% line:83% align:start
I probably couldn't have done
anything to save her.

00:15:47.026 --> 00:15:51.692 position:5% line:77% align:start
And when I think about that it
makes some sort of sense to me.
I can accept it.

00:15:52.026 --> 00:15:56.693 position:5% line:77% align:start
It seems like, for some reason,
I've lost the idea that life is
supposed to be fair.

00:15:57.027 --> 00:16:00.260 position:16% line:77% align:start
I don't see any point in
complaining about the fact that
she died...

00:16:00.293 --> 00:16:02.293 position:21% line:83% align:start
and no one's coming
to help us.

00:16:02.327 --> 00:16:04.559 position:7% line:83% align:start
(YAEKO) <i>That's because you're</i>
 <i>the big brother.</i>

00:16:04.993 --> 00:16:05.693 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:16:06.394 --> 00:16:08.028 position:5% line:89% align:start
For Sheila, and also for Marcos.

00:16:08.961 --> 00:16:10.128 position:55% line:89% align:start
Big brother..?

00:16:11.461 --> 00:16:13.194 position:21% line:83% align:start
(YAEKO) <i>You're the oldest.</i>
 <i>You've taken on that role.</i>

00:16:14.560 --> 00:16:16.794 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>You've helped Marcos and the</i>
 <i>rest of us survive on Mars.</i>

00:16:17.694 --> 00:16:21.595 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>But remember there are older,</i>
 <i>wiser people who can help you.</i>

00:16:21.628 --> 00:16:28.029 position:19% line:77% align:start
(ALEX) <i>Yeah. I guess you're</i>
 <i>right. There's XO Michele,</i>
 <i>Captain Komachi, Akari...</i>

00:16:28.229 --> 00:16:29.062 position:55% line:89% align:start
(YAEKO) <i>And..?</i>

00:16:29.862 --> 00:16:30.628 position:35% line:89% align:start
Who else?

00:16:30.862 --> 00:16:31.828 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hm!

00:16:31.862 --> 00:16:32.695 position:78% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:16:32.728 --> 00:16:34.030 position:30% line:89% align:start
You mean you?!

00:16:35.263 --> 00:16:37.562 position:7% line:83% align:start
(YAEKO) <i>When you got the news</i>
 <i>that Sheila was dead...</i>

00:16:37.763 --> 00:16:39.696 position:5% line:83% align:start
...you represed what you were
feeling.

00:16:40.763 --> 00:16:43.796 position:5% line:83% align:start
But it's okay to cry when you're
hurting, you know?

00:16:43.829 --> 00:16:45.030 position:5% line:89% align:start
The XO said:

00:16:46.230 --> 00:16:48.964 position:5% line:83% align:start
When humans are sad, we cry. If
we're angry we scream...

00:16:49.197 --> 00:16:53.031 position:5% line:77% align:start
and then we tell a joke or two
to put laughter back in our
lives.

00:16:53.064 --> 00:16:55.964 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Remember, your big brother and</i>
 <i>sister are here for you.</i>

00:16:55.997 --> 00:17:02.098 position:5% line:77% align:start
So, come in for a hug and a cry.
I'm only charging 5000 yen a
hug. Come to big sis...

00:17:02.132 --> 00:17:03.332 position:38% line:83% align:start
and her
great big bossom!

00:17:03.365 --> 00:17:04.265 position:83% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:17:04.298 --> 00:17:05.065 position:5% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:17:05.098 --> 00:17:06.132 position:5% line:89% align:start
Was that too much?

00:17:06.165 --> 00:17:08.332 position:5% line:89% align:start
Okay, how about 4000 yen?

00:17:08.365 --> 00:17:12.598 position:19% line:77% align:start
Wait, I'm sorry I don't
understand what you're talking
about. Like...

00:17:12.631 --> 00:17:14.033 position:61% line:83% align:start
who's my big
sister?

00:17:14.066 --> 00:17:16.832 position:5% line:83% align:start
I am! Alex, you're 18 years old,
right?

00:17:16.866 --> 00:17:19.133 position:10% line:83% align:start
Yeah... Wait you're older than
me?!

00:17:19.166 --> 00:17:21.866 position:13% line:83% align:start
That's right! Can't you tell?
I'm twenty!

00:17:22.766 --> 00:17:31.334 position:7% line:77% align:start
Oh...uh... [chuckle] Seriously?
[laughing] No way you're older
than me.

00:17:31.367 --> 00:17:34.600 position:5% line:83% align:start
That's rude, y'know. You thought
I was younger than you?

00:17:34.633 --> 00:17:36.933 position:19% line:89% align:start
M-hm. And less mature, too.

00:17:36.967 --> 00:17:38.833 position:5% line:89% align:start
[gasp] You little brat!

00:17:38.867 --> 00:17:40.801 position:19% line:89% align:start
I'm older, and more mature!

00:17:40.834 --> 00:17:44.101 position:13% line:83% align:start
But... my M.A.R.S. Ranking is
lower than yours.

00:17:44.135 --> 00:17:47.201 position:5% line:89% align:start
[chuckling]

00:17:47.801 --> 00:17:48.335 position:72% line:89% align:start
[crying]

00:17:48.368 --> 00:17:49.101 position:5% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:17:49.135 --> 00:17:51.601 position:38% line:89% align:start
[crying]

00:17:51.801 --> 00:17:52.768 position:5% line:89% align:start
[sigh]

00:17:52.801 --> 00:17:54.302 position:72% line:89% align:start
[crying]

00:17:54.336 --> 00:17:56.269 position:5% line:89% align:start
That's right... Let it out.

00:17:56.302 --> 00:18:00.369 position:38% line:89% align:start
[crying]

00:18:00.403 --> 00:18:03.802 position:10% line:83% align:start
I just kind of leapt out to
catch you without thinking.

00:18:05.735 --> 00:18:09.569 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'm sorry, Yaeko. Don't worry
about me. Save yourself and run.

00:18:09.970 --> 00:18:11.603 position:13% line:89% align:start
You've got your serum, right?

00:18:12.170 --> 00:18:12.903 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh-huh.

00:18:13.903 --> 00:18:15.603 position:5% line:83% align:start
If you can mutate and get out of
here somehow...

00:18:15.636 --> 00:18:18.037 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's gonna be okay, Alex.

00:18:19.370 --> 00:18:20.704 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's okay.

00:18:22.604 --> 00:18:26.271 position:5% line:83% align:start
There's someone here...
[whimpering]

00:18:26.871 --> 00:18:29.204 position:5% line:83% align:start
...someone who can keep <i>you</i>
safe, for a change.

00:18:31.637 --> 00:18:33.038 position:27% line:89% align:start
Yaeko, what do you mean?

00:18:34.339 --> 00:18:38.205 position:5% line:83% align:start
You smell so wondeful right now.
You know that?

00:18:38.938 --> 00:18:40.139 position:58% line:89% align:start
I smell good?

00:18:41.305 --> 00:18:45.272 position:13% line:83% align:start
No, I smell terrible. I'm all
sweat and Martian dirt.

00:18:45.305 --> 00:18:46.538 position:5% line:89% align:start
No, you're wrong.

00:18:47.672 --> 00:18:50.273 position:5% line:83% align:start
To me, you smell like bright
sunshine on a beautiful day.

00:18:50.306 --> 00:18:51.639 position:78% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:18:51.672 --> 00:18:54.040 position:5% line:89% align:start
Artificial metamorphosis!

00:18:55.873 --> 00:18:59.606 position:21% line:89% align:start
[grunts and growls]

00:19:07.874 --> 00:19:08.707 position:5% line:89% align:start
What are you?

00:19:09.907 --> 00:19:11.540 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm the one who stinks.

00:19:13.074 --> 00:19:17.708 position:13% line:83% align:start
I am M.A.R.S. Ranking 98...
Procedure base. striped skunk!

00:19:18.908 --> 00:19:21.075 position:7% line:89% align:start
What's wrong? Too much for you?

00:19:21.108 --> 00:19:23.875 position:7% line:5% align:start
Get any closer and I'll make it
even worse!

00:19:25.208 --> 00:19:27.809 position:10% line:5% align:start
Come on, let's scram while the
stench has them distracted.

00:19:27.842 --> 00:19:28.343 position:21% line:89% align:start
[grunts and groans]

00:19:28.376 --> 00:19:29.043 position:5% line:89% align:start
Y-yeah.

00:19:29.976 --> 00:19:32.243 position:5% line:89% align:start
You're amazing, Yaeko. Really.

00:19:32.276 --> 00:19:33.709 position:61% line:89% align:start
Wow, really?

00:19:33.976 --> 00:19:35.942 position:5% line:89% align:start
Yeah, amazingly smelly.

00:19:35.976 --> 00:19:36.276 position:75% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:19:37.443 --> 00:19:38.942 position:13% line:83% align:start
I mean honestly, did you piss
your pants or something?

00:19:40.777 --> 00:19:43.777 position:7% line:77% align:start
How dare you I would never...
Well, maybe a little..? Wait,
no! This is how my power works!

00:19:43.810 --> 00:19:48.244 position:10% line:77% align:start
It smells like a mix between
gross asparagus and rotten eggs
and a bunch of other aweful...

00:19:48.277 --> 00:19:49.044 position:75% line:89% align:start
things.

00:19:50.110 --> 00:19:51.877 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'm glad you're a bird with a
bad sense of smell.

00:19:52.210 --> 00:19:53.210 position:55% line:89% align:start
But you stink.

00:19:54.778 --> 00:19:57.577 position:16% line:77% align:start
Almost there. A little
farther... We have to move now,
while they're off guard.

00:19:58.045 --> 00:19:59.311 position:66% line:89% align:start
We did it!

00:19:59.345 --> 00:20:00.211 position:27% line:89% align:start
[pained grunts]

00:20:02.211 --> 00:20:03.045 position:30% line:89% align:start
[pained groan]

00:20:03.378 --> 00:20:04.078 position:35% line:89% align:start
Yaeko..!?

00:20:04.778 --> 00:20:05.544 position:27% line:89% align:start
[pained whimper]

00:20:08.046 --> 00:20:12.212 position:10% line:83% align:start
[pained whimpers] It hurts!
[screming]

00:20:12.246 --> 00:20:13.046 position:75% line:89% align:start
Yaeko!?

00:20:13.745 --> 00:20:16.046 position:13% line:89% align:start
It hurts, oh it hurts so bad!

00:20:21.613 --> 00:20:22.280 position:41% line:89% align:start
Jooji!

00:20:31.780 --> 00:20:34.014 position:16% line:89% align:start
[grunt] What the--? Huh?

00:20:34.048 --> 00:20:34.647 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:20:35.214 --> 00:20:36.214 position:19% line:89% align:start
[grunt] Is this water?

00:20:37.947 --> 00:20:40.614 position:13% line:83% align:start
Where did they... get that
ability?

00:20:40.981 --> 00:20:45.547 position:21% line:89% align:start
Joo... Joo... Joo...

00:20:47.615 --> 00:20:48.215 position:41% line:89% align:start
Joo...

00:20:50.015 --> 00:20:51.615 position:21% line:89% align:start
[grunts and groans]

00:20:52.681 --> 00:20:58.015 position:27% line:89% align:start
[pained grunts]

00:20:58.049 --> 00:21:01.283 position:27% line:89% align:start
[groaning] Alex!

00:21:02.183 --> 00:21:02.949 position:30% line:89% align:start
[coughing up]

00:21:02.983 --> 00:21:03.616 position:5% line:89% align:start
Alex!

00:21:03.649 --> 00:21:09.649 position:5% line:89% align:start
[crying]

00:21:09.682 --> 00:21:10.183 position:5% line:5% align:start
Joo.

00:21:13.783 --> 00:21:15.550 position:5% line:89% align:start
(AKARI) <i>Yaeko?! Alex?!</i>

00:21:17.017 --> 00:21:21.717 position:5% line:5% align:start
 <i>Damn it all! We need you...</i>
 <i>Where on this god-forsaken</i>
 <i>planet are you? </i>

00:21:22.051 --> 00:21:27.117 position:10% line:5% align:start
 <i>What's taking you so</i>
 <i>long? Joe! Your M.A.R.S.</i>
 <i>Ranking is...</i>

00:21:27.151 --> 00:21:39.751 position:72% line:89% align:start
[crying]

00:21:39.785 --> 00:21:44.053 position:16% line:89% align:start
Please no! No, please! Nooo!

00:21:48.319 --> 00:21:51.886 position:24% line:89% align:start
W-what? How did...? What?

00:21:58.120 --> 00:21:59.220 position:50% line:89% align:start
Don't you worry.

00:22:00.354 --> 00:22:02.220 position:13% line:83% align:start
